# Tailnet-only Caddy example for NRD
# ----------------------------------
# Purpose:
#   - Expose NRD only to devices on your Tailscale network.
#   - Keep NRD off the public internet.
#
# Replace these before use:
#   - nrd.example.ts.net  -> your real MagicDNS name
#   - 100.64.0.10         -> your droplet's real Tailscale IPv4 from 'tailscale ip -4'
#
# Browser URL from another device on your Tailnet:
#   http://nrd.example.ts.net
#
# Typical NRD runtime for this mode:
#   HOST=127.0.0.1 PORT=8080 cargo run
#
# Notes:
#   - Caddy listens only on the Tailscale interface with 'bind'.
#   - Because auto_https is off here, use http, not https.
{
    auto_https off
}

http://nrd.example.ts.net {
    bind 100.64.0.10
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}
